	abstract = {In this article, we tackle for the first time the problem of dynamic memory-efficient Searchable Symmetric Encryption (SSE). In the term ‚Äúmemory-efficient‚Äù SSE, we encompass both the goals of local SSE, and page-efficient SSE. The centerpiece of our approach is a novel connection between those two goals. We introduce a map, called the Generic Local Transform, which takes as input a page-efficient SSE scheme with certain special features, and outputs an SSE scheme with strong locality properties. We obtain several results. (1) First, for page-efficient SSE with page size p, we build a dynamic scheme with storage efficiency \$\${\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}(\{1\})\$\$O(1)and page efficiency \$\${\textbackslash}widetilde\{{\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}\}{\textbackslash}left( \{{\textbackslash}textrm\{log\}{\textbackslash}, {\textbackslash}textrm\{log\}{\textbackslash}, (N/p)\}{\textbackslash}right) \$\$O{\textasciitilde}loglog(N/p), called \$\${\textbackslash}textsf\{LayeredSSE\}\$\$LayeredSSE. The main technical innovation behind \$\${\textbackslash}textsf\{LayeredSSE\}\$\$LayeredSSEis a novel weighted extension of the two-choice allocation process, of independent interest. (2) Second, we introduce the Generic Local Transform, and combine it with \$\${\textbackslash}textsf\{LayeredSSE\}\$\$LayeredSSEto build a dynamic SSE scheme with storage efficiency \$\${\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}(\{1\})\$\$O(1), locality \$\${\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}(\{1\})\$\$O(1), and read efficiency \$\${\textbackslash}widetilde\{{\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}\}{\textbackslash}left( \{{\textbackslash}textrm\{log\}{\textbackslash},{\textbackslash}textrm\{log\}{\textbackslash}, N\}{\textbackslash}right) \$\$O{\textasciitilde}loglogN, under the condition that the longest list is of size \$\${\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}(\{N{\textasciicircum}\{1-1/{\textbackslash}textrm\{log\}{\textbackslash}, {\textbackslash}textrm\{log\}{\textbackslash}, {\textbackslash}lambda \}\})\$\$O(N1-1/loglogŒª). This matches, in every respect, the purely static construction of Asharov et al. presented at STOC 2016: dynamism comes at no extra cost. (3) Finally, by applying the Generic Local Transform to a variant of the Tethys scheme by Bossuat et al. from Crypto 2021, we build an unconditional static SSE with storage efficiency \$\${\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}(\{1\})\$\$O(1), locality \$\${\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}(\{1\})\$\$O(1), and read efficiency \$\${\textbackslash}mathcal \{O\}(\{{\textbackslash}textrm\{log\}{\textasciicircum}{\textbackslash}varepsilon N\})\$\$O(logŒµN), for an arbitrarily small constant \$\${\textbackslash}varepsilon {\textgreater} 0\$\$Œµ{\textgreater}0. To our knowledge, this is the construction that comes closest to the lower bound presented by Cash and Tessaro at Eurocrypt 2014.},
